See ../README for common README about the test-suite.

The Kotlin test-suite uses one directory per test case as each test case
uses its own Kotlin/Java package named after the test case. All the
generated Kotlin files for a test case are compiled with a single kotlinc
invocation as the Kotlin compiler startup overhead is significant.

A test case is run if a file named after the test case with a _runme.kt
suffix exists. The runme file must select its JVM class name with a
@file:JvmName("testcase_runme") annotation as the default Kotlin file
facade class name capitalizes the first letter of the file name. The
compiled runme is executed with the kotlin launcher that ships with the
Kotlin compiler so that the Kotlin runtime is on the classpath.

The Kotlin module is experimental and large parts of the test-suite are
expected to fail. Failing tests should be added to the FAILING_CPP_TESTS
and FAILING_C_TESTS lists in Makefile.in as they are found.
